Class JSONMultiObject

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractMap<K,V>

        • org.json.simple.JSONObject
          • gw.pl.util.JSONMultiObject
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.util.Map, org.json.simple.JSONAware, org.json.simple.JSONStreamAware

    public class JSONMultiObject
extends org.json.simple.JSONObject
    JSONObject derivative that supports multiple values for a single key. Good enough for read only operations, but may not produce intuitive or correct results if performing mixed operations (adds and removes against a single key). For use interpreting JSON from Solr as Solr bulk messages have multiple values for the same key. See http://wiki.apache.org/solr/UpdateJSON To use this class, use a JSONParser instance configured with JSONMultiKeyContainerFactory, e.g. Object result = new JSONParser(). parse(jsonString, new JSONMultiKeyContainerFactory())
